# TRENDS WE'RE FOLLOWING

[The Times Does a 180](https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/24/magazine/youth-mental-health-crisis-schools.html) - Three weeks before publishing their homeschool piece, the New York Times Magazine ran "America's Children Are Unwell. Are Schools Part of the Problem?" One in four seventeen-year-old boys now diagnosed with ADHD. Autism diagnoses went from 1 in 2,500 in the 1980s to 1 in 31 today. Anxiety diagnoses in 32% of adolescents - median onset age of six. Peter Gray, quoted in the piece: "Instead of saying, 'We need to fix the schools,' the message is, 'We need to fix the kids.'" ([NYT Magazine](https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/24/magazine/youth-mental-health-crisis-schools.html))

[Readers Are Now the Minority](https://x.com/paulg/status/2000671836992884746) - Essayist Paul Graham shares data: "Readers used to outnumber non-readers 2 to 1. Now non-readers outnumber readers 3 to 1." That's a complete inversion. Hard to imagine a shift that big not showing up everywhere. ([Paul Graham](https://x.com/paulg/status/2000671836992884746))

[Parents Want Skills, Not Just Scores](https://www.edchoice.org/2026-fall-polling-finds-parents-value-durable-skills-development-in-schools/) - EdChoice polling finds 85% of parents rate "durable skills" - communication, critical thinking, teamwork, adaptability - as extremely or very important. 45% say a school's emphasis on these makes a "significant" impact on enrollment. Meanwhile, 73% of school parents now support Education Savings Accounts. ([EdChoice](https://www.edchoice.org/2026-fall-polling-finds-parents-value-durable-skills-development-in-schools/))

[Teachers and Students See Different Realities](https://www.the74million.org/article/student-engagement-is-key-defining-and-measuring-it-is-the-challenge/) - 92% of students say engaging lessons make school more enjoyable, but only 63% say they feel "highly engaged." There's a 20-point gap between what students report and what teachers perceive. The report's conclusion: engagement isn't optional - it's a precondition for learning. ([The 74](https://www.the74million.org/article/student-engagement-is-key-defining-and-measuring-it-is-the-challenge/))

[The 8-Hour Day Is Made Up](https://x.com/AdamMGrant/status/1192198752527929345) - We talk a lot about how the six-hour school day is an artifact of the factory model. But what about the eight-hour workday? Organizational psychologist Adam Grant: "The 8-hour work day was not ordained from above for all time. It was dreamed up by humans. We can be as productive and creative in 6 focused hours as in 8 unfocused hours." Anyone who's watched their kid finish "a full day of school" in two hours at home already knows this. ([Adam Grant](https://x.com/AdamMGrant/status/1192198752527929345))

